{"question": "{"scenario": "", "healthText": "Which tests or examination to do to confirm wetin dey cause di pain?\r\nWetin be di treatment plan?", "difficulty": "Medium", "language": "Pidgin", "userId": "", "topic": ""}", "answer": "This is a case of Acute Gingivitis with or without Parotitis.
Patient should be treated using the following;
- Oral Amoxiclav for 1 week to 10 days 
- Oral Prednisolone for 3 days
- Oral Vitamin C
- Rinsing of mouth with warm salt solution "}

{"question": "{"scenario": "", "healthText": "Wetin I go do for dis gal", "difficulty": "Medium", "language": "Pidgin", "userId": "", "topic": ""}", "answer": "This is a case of Dysmenorrhoea; painful menstruation.
Patient should be offered strong analgesics for the pain;
If paracetamol is not enough for the pain; Piroxicam, Diclofenac or Ibuprofen should be used to manage the pain.
If patient would be using this drug for a while or every month; it should be prescribed with omeprazole to protect the stomach lining."}

{"question": "{"scenario": "", "healthText": "Nje apoju eje osoosu ko ni se akoba fun ile Omo omobinrin yi,? Se eje nkan osu yi ko fa airomobi fun obirin yi? Iru ayewo wo ni o le se itoju wo ni o le gba,ati pe ona wo ni eje nkan osu yi Fi le diku", "difficulty": "Medium", "language": "Yoruba", "userId": "", "topic": ""}", "answer": "Yes, excessive menstrual bleeding (menorrhagia) can cause problems for a young girl. If she loses too much blood, she may develop anemia, leading to weakness, dizziness, and tiredness. Also, if it continues, it may affect her fertility in the future, depending on the cause.

She needs to see a doctor for tests like a full blood count (FBC) to check for anemia, hormonal tests to rule out hormonal imbalance, and pelvic ultrasound to check for fibroids or ovarian issues. Treatment depends on the cause but may include iron supplements, tranexamic acid to reduce bleeding, or hormonal therapy like combined oral contraceptives. If it's very severe, a gynecologist must be involved.







"}

{"question": "{"scenario": "", "healthText": "Iru ewu wo ni o wa ni ifipabanilopo ati paapaa julo Lai lo roba idabobo ? N je omobinrin yi le tobi ifipabanilopo yi ni Arun kogboogun tabi loyun? Iru itoju wo ni o le gba ni kiakia lati Dena oyun ati Arun,", "difficulty": "Hard", "language": "Yoruba", "userId": "umuabdullahigbeko2024@gmail.com", "topic": "Ifipabanilopo "}", "answer": "Risks of Rape Without Protection: Includes sexually transmitted infections (STIs), unwanted pregnancy, physical injuries, and psychological trauma (PTSD, depression, anxiety).

Can She Get an Incurable Disease or Pregnant? Yes, she is at risk of HIV, hepatitis B, gonorrhea, chlamydia, and pregnancy.

Immediate Care: Provide emergency contraception (within 72 hours), post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP) for HIV, antibiotics for STIs, tetanus vaccine if needed, and psychological support."}

{"question": "{"scenario": "", "healthText": "Se aisan typhoid le fa ki eyan maa bi?\r\n\r\nSe Mo Le se ayewo malaria fun obinrin yi?\r\n\r\nBawo ni mo sele din Ara gbigbona omobinrin yi ku?", "difficulty": "Medium", "language": "Yoruba", "userId": "", "topic": ""}", "answer": "Typhoid can cause vomiting 

Malaria parasite test should be done 

Antipyretics can be administered to break the fever oral, IM or IV paracetamol "}
